{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, they used three items with the stem 'For me, eating healthy foods in the next few weeks would be...' and seven-point response scales anchored by not worthwhile/worthwhile; bad/good; and not beneficial/beneficial.",
    "Despite not having explicated attitude definitions available, these descriptions illustrate the heterogeneity in the implicit definitions of the attitude construct.",
    "The HRAS-13 items assess the importance of a person's health, the subjective evaluation of taking care of one's body, and the impression of other people's evaluations of one's risk taking behavior (Huls et al., 2022).",
    "The corresponding definition of attitude seems to contain elements of risk perception, social norms, and importance.",
    "These elements seem absent from the definition used by Taylor et al. (2022), which instead contains elements of trust and moral norms."
  ]
}